        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> \"vim.pack\" was not a thing back then and was added to example_init.lua later in #34009.\r\n\r\nDoesn't matter, I could have made example_init.lua use lazy.nvim, like kickstart.nvim anyway\r\n\r\n> By looking at PR you provided \"kickstart.nvim way\" seems like becoming a distro\r\n\r\nkickstart.nvim also started as one configuration file (even now most of its code is in one file). If Nvim allows example_init to be like this, it will follow kickstart way\r\n\r\n>  I don't think the example config should be perceived as an official recommendation of the \"best\" or must-have plugins.\r\n\r\nA lot of people will think of them as \"must-have plugins\", because otherwise why are they listed there?",
