            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> As long as the plugins are literally not abandoned and works I can't see any objections to edit them\r\n\r\nYes, the idea is to mention a few high-quality, zero-configuration plugins that immediately solve common use-cases.\r\n\r\nquicker.nvim is a great example of a plugin that really enhances Nvim with zero downsides AFAICT (it is surprisingly fast).\r\n\r\nI don't really care about the people that nitpick everything :)",
