            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Yes, the idea is to mention a few high-quality, zero-configuration plugins that immediately solve common use-cases.\r\n\r\nmini.completion require calling `setup()` to work.\r\n\r\nAnd again, why not recommend using built-in autocompletion? If a built-in feature is not recommended to use, shouldn't you remove it, because it will go unmaintained sooner or later. Not to say that many people may think Neovim does not have built-in autocompletion \r\n\r\n> I don't really care about the people that nitpick everything\r\n\r\nI feel like you are one, I saw you sent a lot of docs PR recently",
